		 <style>.__pf  .Title { 	font-family: 'Proxima Nova Lt'; } .__pf  .Body { 	font-family: 'Gotham Book';</style> <style></style><div style="opacity:0" class="sc-AjmGg kONSRg __pf __pf_MzX42YYG" id="__pf"><div data-pf-type="Body" class="sc-dSfdvi hbFSvJ pf-1_"><div data-pf-type="Layout" class="sc-bUbRBg Gdkwx pf-2_"><div data-section-id="pf-ca10" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jivBlf inQyRG pf-3_"><div class="sc-dkQkyq kCnPmW"><div class="sc-cNKqjZ PEdbg pf-4_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hZpJaK lYhcR pf-5_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-275_ pf-gs-heading-1 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-274_">Urtopia Privacy Policy</span></h1></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-03fc" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jivBlf inQyRG pf-9_"><div style="--cw:820px" class="sc-dkQkyq kCnPmW"><div class="sc-cNKqjZ PEdbg pf-10_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hZpJaK lYhcR pf-11_"><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-12_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-14_">This Privacy Policy explains how New Urtopia Holdings HK Limited (“Urtopia”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses, shares and processes your personal data as well as the rights and choices you have associated with that data.Urtopia is committed to protecting your privacy and personal data. We encourage you to read this Privacy Policy to understand what we do with the personal data we collect from you and how we keep you safe. This Privacy Policy applies to the use of Urtopia website, App and products (collectively, the “Services”), effective from March 14, 2022.From time to time, you may be able to follow a link to the websites or services of other companies or individuals from our website or our App. These companies or individuals may collect your personal data in accordance with their own privacy policies. Urtopia’s Privacy Policy does not extend to these external websites, services and third parties.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-15_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-17_">This Privacy Policy Discusses:</span></h2><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-305_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-283_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-282_">How We Collect and Use Personal Data</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-286_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-285_">How We Share Personal Data We Collect</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-289_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-288_">Our Data Security and Storage Practices</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-292_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-291_">How We Store and Transfer Your Personal Data</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-295_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-294_">Your Choices Regarding the Use of Your Personal Data</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-298_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-297_">Minors’ Personal Data</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-301_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-300_">Privacy Policy Updates</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-304_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-303_">How You Can Contact Us</span></li></ul><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-43_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-45_">We have tried to keep this policy as simple and easy-to-read as possible. If you have any questions, please contact us at <a href="/pages/contactus" target="_self">support@newurtopia.com.</a></span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-46_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-48_">1. How We Collect and Use Personal Data</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-49_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-51_">In this privacy policy, personal data means any data relating to an identified or identifiable natural person as defined in the law of the country or region of your residence.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-52_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-54_">1.1 We Collect Personal Data When You Use Our Website</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-55_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-57_">When you use our website, we may collect a variety of personal data from or about you to provide services to you. For example,</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-58_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-59_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-61_">When you purchase Urtopia’s products from our website, we will collect and use your name, phone number, address, e-mail address to fulfill your request for products, or to send you notifications, confirmations, updates, product announcements, and security alerts. We may also use such personal data to create an account for you. If you are a resident of European Economic Area (“EEA”), we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”), i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-62_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-64_">When you register on the mailing list or for our newsletter, your email address will be added to our contact list. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of the GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-65_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-67_">When you send us an email to participate in our surveys, request help from customer support, or otherwise submit information to us through our website, in order to respond to your communications and requests, provide customer service, request feedback, and otherwise contact you about your use of our Service, we may collect your e-mail and other personal data that you directly provide to us, such as your name, telephone number and address. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-68_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-70_">When you request an exchange or refund, we may collect additional personal data about payment details and reasons for requesting an exchange or refund. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-71_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-73_">When you use our website, we may collect your browsing behaviors to improve the performance or design of our website. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-74_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-76_">When you use any of the public comment or interactive features of our website, we may collect any information you provide to us. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.&nbsp;</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-77_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-79_">1.2 We Collect Personal Data When You Use Our App and Products</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-80_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-82_">Urtopia is proud of its futuristic design and smart functions. When you use our App and our products, or when you connect your bike with your Urtopia Account, we may collect your personal data to provide services to you. Depending on which services or features you request or use, not all of these types of personal data may be applicable to you.&nbsp;</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-83_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-84_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-86_">When you sign up for a Urtopia Account (“Account”), you may provide us with a combination of personal data, such as your e-mail, name or nickname, and password. You may also choose to provide us with additional personal data, such as your phone number, address, birthday, and gender. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-87_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-89_">You may provide location data of the e-bike to us, which is necessary to enable navigation, anti-theft and find-my-bike functions. For navigation purpose and find-my-bike functions, if you are a resident of EEA, we process such location data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract. For anti-theft purpose, if you are a resident of EEA, we process such location data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-90_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-92_">We may use your fingerprint information to enable you to unlock your bike, and such information is only stored on your bike and will not be transferred to us. You can also use your cellphone to unlock your bike, and we may use your Bluetooth information to provide such feature. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-93_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-95_">You can interact with the e-bike by pressing a certain button and speaking to it. We may capture audio voice recordings and voice commands during those interactions. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract. We cannot prevent you from providing additional personal data when you interact with the e-bike.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-96_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-98_">We may collect your audio voice recordings and voice commands, when you use voice control feature in your e-bike. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-99_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-101_">Our e-bike carries a bunch of IoT sensors including torque sensor, gyroscope, mm-wave radar and GPS. You may sync data collected from such sensors and other bike stats data, such as, speed, distance, battery level, boot screen, ringing sound, motor power, slope, etc. to your Account on our App. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract. We may use such data to improve your riding experience and to provide more fascinating features on our App. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-102_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-104_">We may collect device numbers of your e-bike, such as hardware serial number, MAC address, and unique device identifier to check status of your e-bike when you request for after-sales service and provide relevant service to you. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-105_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-107_">1.3 How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-108_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-110_">Like most web-based services, we automatically receive and record information on our server logs from your browser when you use our website. We may use a variety of methods, including beacons and cookies, to collect your personal data. The personal data that we collect with these automated methods may include, for example, your IP address, cookie data, a unique device or user ID, browser type, system type, the content and pages that you access on our website, and the “referring URL” (that is, the page from which you navigated to our website). Please see our cookie policy for more details.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-111_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-113_">1.4 We Collect Personal Data from Third Parties</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-114_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-116_">To the extent permitted by applicable law, we may combine personal data with other personal data we collect from your activity in our Services, personal data we receive from other companies or publicly available personal data.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-117_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-119_">1.5 We Aggregate and Anonymize Personal Data</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-120_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-122_">We may use personal data we collect in aggregated forms. That is, we may combine personal data about our users with that of others in an anonymous manner to create aggregate data. Aggregate data does not contain or constitute personal data. In such cases, there will be no identifying data disclosed about you. When we entrust non-Urtopia companies to anonymize or aggregate data on our behalf, we will oversee their personal data processing through contractual arrangements to ensure adequate protection of your personal data. We will not identify your identity, except in accordance with this Privacy Policy. We do not sell personalized demographic data or user data.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-123_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-125_">1.6 Public Comment and User Generated Content</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-126_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-128_">We provide public comment features and other interactive features to share user generated content on our website and App. Please note that any information you post or disclose using this feature will become public information, and will be available to other users of our Services and to the general public. We urge you to be very careful when deciding to disclose your personal data, or any other information. If you provide feedback to us, we may use and disclose such feedback on our website, provided we do not associate such feedback with your personal data. If you have provided your consent to do so, we may post your first and last name along with your feedback on our website. We will collect any information contained in such feedback and will treat the personal data in it in accordance with this Policy.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-129_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-131_">2. How We Share Personal Data We Collect</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-132_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-134_">We are committed to protecting data that identifies you personally, where you have chosen to keep it private. We will only share your personal data in the following circumstances:<br><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">With Urtopia service providers.</span>  Urtopia hires several service providers to help operate our Services (including vendors and payment processors), and may give access to certain personal data necessary for service providers to undertake their work, in which case we will require those service providers to honor the privacy and your personal data. Urtopia currently uses the following third-party service providers to provide their services:<br></span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-135_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-136_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-138_">Vendors who provide platform service. Our website is hosted on Shopify Inc. Shopify provides us with the online e-commerce platform that allows us to sell our products to you. Your personal data may be stored through Shopify’s data storage and databases. For more insight, you may also want to read Shopify’s Terms of Service or Privacy Policy.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-139_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-141_">Vendors who provide delivery service. We may share your contact information, such as address and phone number with these vendors to fulfill delivering products.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-142_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-144_">Vendors who provide voice recognition technology. We may share your audio voice recordings with these vendors to generate voice commands and enable you to use voice control features.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-145_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-147_">Vendors who provide email service. We may share your e-mail address with these vendors, such as MailChimp, to send you marketing messages, notifications, confirmations, updates, product announcements, and security alerts.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-148_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-150_">Vendors who provide analytics services. Our website uses analytics services, such as Fabric, a software development and integration kit that allows Urtopia to analyze its customers’ general usage patterns, including the rates of Urtopia users on daily and weekly bases.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-151_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-153_">Vendors who provide payment service. Our website uses Klarna for alternative payment options. You can read more about how Klarna uses your personal information here: <a href="https://www.klarna.com/international/privacy-policy/" target="_blank">https://www.klarna.com/international/privacy-policy/</a></span></li></ul><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-154_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-156_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">With Urtopia partners. We may share some of your personal data with our partners (including a parent company, subsidiaries, other companies that we control or that are under common control with us, and joint venture partners), in which case we will require those partners to honor your personal data.<br><br>In the event of merger or sale. If Urtopia is involved in a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or any form of sale of some or all of its business, personal data may be transferred with the business.<br><br>When legally obligated or to protect from harm. Urtopia may share personal data when we have a good faith that access, use, preservation or disclosure of the personal data is reasonably necessary to (a) satisfy any requirement of law, regulation, legal process or enforceable governmental request; (b) enforce or investigate a potential violation of the Terms of Use; (c) detect, prevent or otherwise respond to fraud, security or technical concerns; or (d) protect the rights, property or safety of Urtopia, its users or the public against harm.<br></span></span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-157_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-159_">3. Our Data Security and Storage Practices</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-160_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-162_">We work hard to protect Urtopia and our users from unauthorized access to or unauthorized alteration, disclosure or destruction of personal data we hold. Urtopia follows industry standards and best practices to help protect your personal data from unauthorized access, use and disclosure. For example, we store the personal data we collect on computer systems with limited access and located in controlled facilities. When we transmit highly-confidential personal data over the Internet, we protect it through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol. Please be aware that, despite our efforts, no security measures are impenetrable. Unfortunately, we cannot guarantee that any method of data transmission will protect against any interception or other type of misuse.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-163_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-165_">4. How We Store and Transfer Your Personal Data</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-166_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-168_">Urtopia stores and processes personal data in databases hosted in the country or region in compliance with applicable laws. We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected and to the extent permitted or required by law.&nbsp;<br><br>In some circumstances, we will, subject to law, transfer your personal data to other countries or regions where you reside or allow entities outside of countries or regions where you reside to access your personal data. Any such transfer of your personal data will be carried out in compliance with applicable laws.<br></span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-329_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-328_">5. Your Choices Regarding the Use of Your Personal Data</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-172_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-174_">You may request access to and correction of your personal data we retain. If you request that we delete personal data, such personal data will be permanently deleted, and we will no longer retain that personal data in any form. If you wish to stop further collection or use of your personal data, or to delete your email address, you may choose to permanently delete your Account by emailing us at support@newurtopia.com. Please note that, by permanently deleting your Account, you will disable most of the advanced functionality of the Urtopia e-bike. To reinstate functionality at a later date, you may set up a new Account. You may also opt out of receiving emails from us anytime by following the unsubscribe instructions in those emails.<br><br>In addition, depending on applicable law, you have the right to submit a complaint or object to our collection and use of your information at any time, or to require us to review, transmit, change, or delete your personal data that we have collected and retained. We will fulfill your request to exercise any of these rights within the applicable time period subscribed by such laws. You can exercise these rights, express concerns, or obtain additional information about the use of your personal data by contacting us.&nbsp;<br></span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-175_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-177_">5.1 Your rights under GDPR or Data Protection Act 2018</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-178_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-180_">If you are a resident in the EEA or the United Kingdom, you have the following rights:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-181_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-182_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-184_">Right to Access. You may request access to the personal data we process about you;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-185_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-187_">Right to Correct and Delete. You may request us to correct, update, shield or delete your personal data in our records;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-188_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-190_">Right to Request a Copy. You may request a copy of the personal data we have processed about you. We can - on your request - send this copy to another party, so you don’t have to send the personal data yourself;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-191_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-193_">Object to processing. You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data and request us to cease processing of it if, for example, this data is being processed for the purpose of direct marketing or where we are relying on a legitimate interest (or those of a third party). In some cases, we may demonstrate that we have compelling legitimate grounds to process your data which override your rights and freedoms.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-194_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-196_">Restrict the processing. This enables you to ask us to suspend the processing of your personal data in the following scenarios: (a) if you want us to establish the accuracy of the personal data; (b) where our use of the data is unlawful but you do not want us to erase it; (c) where you require us to hold the data even if we no longer need it as you require it to establish, exercise or defend legal claims; or (d) you have objected to our use of your data but we need to verify whether we have overriding legitimate grounds to use it.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-197_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-199_">Right to Complain. You may file a complaint against processing your personal data. And you may file a complaint if you are under the impression that we process your data unlawfully;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-200_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-202_">Withdraw Your Consent. You may always withdraw your consent to process your personal data. In that case, we will no longer process your personal data for the purpose for which consent is necessary.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-203_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-205_">Requesting channels. Please email us at support@newurtopia.com to submit your data request.</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-206_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-208_">5.2 California Privacy Rights</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-209_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-211_">Urtopia adopted this section to comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”) and the California Privacy Rights Act (“CPRA”), and applies solely to residents of the State of California (“California Consumers”). Without limiting the foregoing, this section provides California Consumers with the disclosures and notices required under the CCPA. Certain exceptions and limitations may apply to a California Consumer’s rights and Urtopia’s obligations under the CCPA.</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-212_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-213_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-215_">No Sale of Personal Data. If Urtopia ever chooses to sell personal data, you would have the right to opt out of the sale of your personal data.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-216_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-218_">Right to Disclosure. California Consumers have the right to request that we disclose certain data about our collection and use of your personal data over the past 12 months.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-219_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-221_">Right to Access. You have the right to request that we provide you with access to specific pieces of personal data we have collected about you over the past 12 months (also called a “data portability request”).</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-222_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-224_">Right to Deletion. You have the right to request that we delete any of your personal data that we collected from you and retained, with certain exceptions.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-225_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-227_">Right to Correct. You have the right to request us to correct inaccurate personal data if and when you learn that we maintain inaccurate personal data about you.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-228_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-230_">Right Against Discrimination. You have the right not to be discriminated against for exercising any of the rights described in this section. We will not discriminate against you for exercising your right.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-231_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-233_">Right to Limit the Use of Sensitive Personal Information. Some of personal data we collect and use in accordance with purposes described in this Privacy Policy might fall into the scope of sensitive personal data as defined by CPRA. The use of such sensitive personal data will be limited to that use that is necessary for us to provide Services to you or perform our duties as required by CCPA and CPRA. If we may use your sensitive personal data for any other purpose, we will inform you and you have the right to limit the use of your sensitive personal data. Upon your request, we will not use your sensitive personal data for the proposed additional purpose.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-234_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-236_">Submit a Consumer Privacy Request. To exercise any of the above rights, please submit a verifiable consumer privacy request to Urtopia by email at support@newurtopia.com.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-237_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-239_">Verification. We cannot respond to your request or provide you with personal data unless we can verify your identity and your authority to make the request and confirm that the personal data relates to you.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-240_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-242_">Authorized Agent. You may make a verifiable consumer request on behalf of your minor child. Otherwise, only you, or a person you have designated in writing as your authorized agent or who is registered with the California Secretary of State to act on your behalf, or to whom you have provided power of attorney pursuant to California Probate Code sections 4000 to 4465 (“Authorized Agent”) may make a verifiable consumer request related to your personal data.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-243_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-245_">Urtopia’s Response. We endeavor to respond to a verifiable consumer request within 45 days of receipt. If we require more time, we will notify you in writing of the reason and extension period. We will deliver our written response by mail or electronically, at your option. Any disclosures we provide will only cover the 12-month period preceding receipt of the verifiable consumer request. If we cannot comply with part or all of your request, we will explain the reasons in our response. We do not charge a fee to process or respond to your verifiable consumer privacy request unless it is excessive, repetitive, or manifestly unfounded. If we determine that the request warrants a fee, we will tell you why we made that decision and provide you with a cost estimate before completing your request.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-246_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-248_">Other California Privacy Rights. California Civil Code sections 1798.83-1798.84 (the Shine the Light Act) entitles California residents to request disclosure regarding personal data sharing with affiliates and/or third parties for marketing purposes. If you are a California resident and you would like to request a copy of this notice, please contact us at support@newurtopia.com with the subject line “Request for California Privacy Data.”</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-369_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-368_">5.3 Nevada Privacy Rights</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-252_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-254_">If you are a Nevada resident and have provided us with any personal identifying data, you may opt-out of sharing your data with third parties if you submit an opt-out request to the following email address: support@newurtopia.com. Please note we do not sell any of your personal data for profit, we do share some data with contracted third parties in order to provide better services and advertising to you. Please allow 60 days for completion of such request.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-255_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-257_">6. Minors’ Personal Data</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-258_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-260_">Our Services are designed for adults, not children. As such, our Services are not intended for children under 16 years of age. No one under age 16 may provide any personal data to us or in our Services. If you are under 16, do not use or provide any data in our Services, make any purchases through our website, use any of the interactive or public comment features of this website or provide any data about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, email address, or any screen name or user name you may use. If we learn we have collected or received personal data from a child under 16 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that data. If you believe we might have any data from or about a child under 16, please contact us at support@newurtopia.com.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-261_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-263_">7. Privacy Policy Updates</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-264_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-266_">We occasionally update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our Services and customer feedback. All such changes to our Services or in how Urtopia use your personal data will be reflected in this Privacy Policy. When we post changes to this Privacy Policy, we will revise the effective date at the beginning of this statement. If there are material changes to this Privacy Policy or in how Urtopia uses your personal data, we will notify you either by prominently posting a notice of such changes prior to implementing the change or by directly sending you a notification. We encourage you to periodically review this Privacy Policy to keep informed about how Urtopia is protecting your personal data.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-267_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-269_">8. How You Can Contact Us</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-270_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-272_">If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or any privacy-related matter, or any concerns about your privacy, or to request access to or deletion of your personal data, please contact us at&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><a href="/pages/contactus" target="_self">support@newurtopia.com.</a></span><br><br>You may also write to us at:<br>New Urtopia Holdings HK Limited <br>Attn: Urtopia Privacy <br>Unit 9043, Room 903-904,<br>9/F, Block B, Chung Mei Centre,<br>15-17 Hing Yip Street,<br>Kwun Tong, <br>Kowloon,<br>Hong Kong</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-cNKqjZ PEdbg pf-277_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hZpJaK lYhcR pf-276_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-321_ pf-gs-heading-1 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-320_">Urtopia Cookie Policy</span></h1><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-326_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-325_">Last Updated: 07, 02, 2023<br>Effective Date: 07, 02, 2023</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-bSqaIl lbVgtz pf-18_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-19_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-21_">I.	What is a cookie</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-22_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-24_">II.	Cookies on our Website</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-25_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-27_">III.	How we use cookies</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-28_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-30_">IV.	How to control and delete cookies</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-31_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-33_">V.	Changes to this Policy</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jvvksu ldtAhU pf-34_ Body"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-36_">VI.	How to contact us</span></li></ul><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-332_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-331_">This Cookie Policy (this “Policy”) describes the different types of cookies and similar technologies that may be applied on the websites of Urtopia ( https://newurtopia.com/) that lead to this Policy (“Website”) provided by New Urtopia Holdings HK Limited(“Urtopia”, “we”, “us”, or “our”). This Policy also clarifies how you can manage these cookies.For a general view of our approach to the privacy of the personal data you pass to us, please see our Privacy Policy.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-335_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-334_">I.	What is a cookie?</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-308_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-307_">A cookie is a data file, which often includes a unique identifier, that is sent to your browser from a web server and is then stored on the hard drive of your computer or on your mobile device that you are using to browse our Website. When you revisit our Website again, or another website that recognises the same cookie, your device is able to communicate with the website and the website can read the information held in that cookie. Cookies are used to make websites work, to improve the efficiency of websites, to improve the user’s experience and to provide usage information on websites. This information should make your website visits more productive by storing and using the information on your website preferences and habits.&nbsp;<br><br>So-called “first-party cookies” are cookies that are served by the entity operating the domain through which the cookie is served. Urtopia own cookies are therefore “first-party cookies”. In case we allow others to service cookies through the Urtopia websites and apps, these cookies are so-called “third-party cookies”. In addition, there is a difference between session cookies and permanent cookies. Session cookies will only exist until you close your browser. Permanent cookies have a longer lifespan and are not automatically deleted once you close your browser.&nbsp;<br><br>Next to cookies, other tracking technologies are used which are similar to cookies. These can include web beacons (also known as pixel tags, web bugs or gifs), tracking URLs or software development kits (“SDKs”). A web beacon is a tiny graphic image of just one pixel that can be delivered to your computer as part of a web page request, in an app, in an advertisement or in an HTML email message. Pixels can be used to retrieve information from your device, such as your device type or operating system, IP address, and time of visit. They are also used to serve and read cookies in your browser. This information is in particular used to evaluate and enhance how our Website functions, to improve your experience on our Website, including to provide you with content customized to your interests. Tracking URLs are used to understand from which referring website the websites or apps are used. SDKs are small pieces of code included in apps, which function like cookies and web beacons.All these technologies are together referred to in this Policy as “cookies”.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-341_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-340_">II.	Cookies on our Website</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-344_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-343_">On our Website, users have the option of agreeing to the use of cookies in principle and thus being able to use all functions of the website without restrictions, the option of not receiving cookies at any time or of personalizing cookies by agreeing to the use of certain cookies. Please be aware that if you do not accept or deactivate the use of cookies that are subject to consent, this may lead to a situation that these cookies cannot do what they are intended for. In particular, if you deactivate functionality cookies, the respective functions of the website cannot be used. Therefore, your consent is required if you want to use certain functions provided by cookies. You have the right to withdraw your consent at any time by modifying your cookie setting as set out in Section “How to control and delete cookies” and “How we use cookies” below.&nbsp;</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-350_ pf-gs-heading-5 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-349_">III.	How we use cookies</span></h2><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-372_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-371_">You can find more information about the categories of cookies we generally use and the purposes for which we use them in the table below. For the individual cookies of each category, we have further set forth the cookie name, a description of what this cookie does, a duration of the operation of the respective cookie, a description of the management of each cookie as well as a link to available external information where appropriate and, if applicable, what personal information is concerned as well as the name of the third party(ies) having access to the cookie.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-gGCDDS giZcCL pf-382_ pf-gs-heading-6 Title"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-381_">CATEGORY 1: STRICTLY NECESSARY COOKIES (SUCH COOKIES ARE EXEMPT FROM CONSENT)</span></h3><p class="sc-jlsrNB ikRhSQ pf-353_ pf-gs-paragraph-2 Body" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gnnDb jPxwVa pf-352_">These are cookies that are required for the operation of a website and therefore disabling these cookies may make our services unavailable. These cookies are used exclusively by Urtopia and no third parties have access to these cookies. Examples are cookies used for online shopping carts or to protect against fraud. We use these cookies on the basis of our legitimate interest and no consent is required for the use of strictly necessary cookies. <br><br>
